                    <div class="col-md-9 col-md-offset-3">
                        <h2 class="section-heading">Description</h2> <span class="reg-provider"> <i class="fa fa-check-square"></i> <span>Regd. Education Provider</span> <a href="https://www.credly.com/badges/cb9cbf68-29f5-4d75-8ac3-fa5b234fada3/public_url" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"> <i class="accrediation-icons acdtn-page acdtn-page-1 nitro-lazy" style="background-image: url(&quot;https://d2o2utebsixu4k.cloudfront.net/assets/icons/acd-sprite.png&quot;);"></i> </a> </span>
                        <div class="editor-content">
                            <p>A certification which greatly validates a business analyst’s skill set and technical expertise is the Project Management Institute-Professional in Business Analysis (PMI-PBA)<sup>®</sup> . This credential demonstrates the holder’s knowledge and skills in business analysis, and ability to competently use BA tools and techniques to enhance project success.</p>
                            <p>The role of a Business Analyst has come to be critically important in the Project Management field. Today, project management practitioners increasingly turn to business analysis to define their business needs, identify risks and opportunities, and create sustainable solutions for business problems.</p>
                            <p>KnowledgeHut’s comprehensive course on PMI-PBA<sup>®</sup> will not only help you gain the certification but also hands-on, practical skills that will help you succeed in your role as a BA. You will learn the discipline of working with stakeholders to define requirements, and shaping the output of projects to deliver the expected benefits. Join today and master the concepts of BA for a defining career!</p>
                            <h6><strong>What you will learn:</strong></h6>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Learn the skills and clarity needed to effectively perform a business analyst’s role</li>
                                <li>Learn the core terminology, principles and practices of Business analysis</li>
                                <li>Follow established standards that are outlined in the PMI Professional in Business Analysis Handbook</li>
                                <li>Achieve reliable, quality results with enhanced efficiency and consistency</li>
                            </ul>
                            <h6>You will also get:</h6>
                            <ul>
                                <li>35 PDUs on completion of 35 hours of training</li>
                                <li>PMI approved courseware<br></li>
                                <li>Assistance with the PMI-PBA<sup>®</sup>Exam Application Form with end-to-end support via phone, email and chat</li>
                                <li>Two Mock Exams to prepare you for the actual exam<br></li>
                            </ul>
